# Aleria V2 — Architecture Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack, SSG)
- React 19, TypeScript 5, Tailwind CSS v4
- Framer Motion for animations
- Lucide React for icons
- Deployment: Vercel

## Design System
Full reference: `DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` at repo root.

### Color Palette
- **Light mode first**. Dark mode only via `.dark` class on specific sections.
- Background: Warm Paper (`#FAF9F5`) — `bg-background`
- Text: Espresso (`#14110e`) — `text-foreground`
- Contrast sections: Desert Sand Light (`#f5edda`) — `bg-muted`
- Brand accents: Mint (`#00f07b`) — `text-brand-mint` / Sand (`#f8e8c6`) — `text-brand-sand`
- Gradient: `gradient-desert-mint` or `text-gradient-desert-mint` — use max 2-3 per page

### Typography
- Headings (h1, h2): **Source Serif 4** (serif) — applied globally in CSS
- Body: **Geist Sans** — `font-sans`
- Never override heading font on individual elements. The CSS handles it.

## File rules
- Max 150 lines per file. Split if larger.
- No barrel exports (index.ts re-exports). Import directly.
- No unused imports, variables, or files. Run `npm run lint` before finishing.

## Styling
- All colors come from CSS custom properties in `globals.css`.
- Use Tailwind utilities that reference tokens (`text-foreground`, `bg-muted`, `border-border/30`).
- Never hardcode color values in components (no `#fff`, `rgb()`, inline `oklch()`).
- Exception: radial gradients for ambient effects may use oklch inline.
- Use opacity modifiers for subtle variants: `text-muted-foreground/70`, `border-border/15`.

## Components

### Marketing primitives (`components/marketing/`)
- `Btn` — Polymorphic button/link. Variants: `primary`, `secondary`, `ghost`. Sizes: `sm`, `default`, `lg`.
- `Section` — Section wrapper. Props: `background` (`default`/`muted`/`dark`), `spacing`, `divider`.
- `Container` — Max-width wrapper. Props: `size` (`default`/`narrow`/`wide`/`full`).
- `Badge` — Section label. Plain text, no borders.
- `LinkArrow` — Text link with animated arrow.
- `MediaFrame` — Video/image placeholder.

### Sections (`components/sections/{page}/`)
- One file per section, named by content.
- Each section receives `{ className?: string }` via `SectionProps`.
- Use `Section` + `Container` wrappers.

### Layout (`components/layout/`)
- `header.tsx`, `footer.tsx`, `mobile-nav.tsx`
- Logo: `/public/logo.svg` (light) and `/public/logo-dark.svg` (dark sections)

## Animations
- Framer Motion `whileInView` for scroll-triggered.
- Ease: `[0.4, 0, 0.2, 1]`
- Duration: `0.5` (standard), `0.6` (hero/cta)
- Viewport: `{{ once: true, margin: "-80px" }}`
- Lists: `variants` + `staggerChildren: 0.08–0.12`

## What NOT to do
- Do NOT use Shadcn components on marketing pages.
- Do NOT add icon-in-a-box patterns. Use typography and whitespace.
- Do NOT add `"use client"` unless the component uses hooks or event handlers.
- Do NOT create hooks or utilities unless they're used by 2+ files.
- Do NOT use the gradient on buttons, section backgrounds, or more than 3 elements per page.

## Key Files
- Design system reference: `DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`
- CSS tokens: `src/app/globals.css`
- Fonts: `src/lib/fonts.ts`
- Site config: `src/config/site.ts`
- Types: `src/types/index.ts`
